---
import Base from "@/layouts/Base.astro";
import SideBar from "@/components/HelpSidebar.astro";
import HelpTocMobile from "@/components/HelpTocMobile.astro";
import "@/styles/help.scss";

const description = "Help and tips for using the Shelf Talkers app.";
---

<Base pageTitle="Help" description={description} prefetch="">
  <header>
    <nav>
      <a href="/">Home</a>
    </nav>
    <h1>Help</h1>
  </header>
  <main id="main">
    <HelpTocMobile />
    <SideBar>
      <nav class="toc">
        <a href="#basics">Basic Usage</a>
        <a href="#print">Print</a>
        <a href="#font">Change font</a>
        <a href="#logo">Change logo</a>
        <a href="#privacy">Privacy</a>
      </nav>
    </SideBar>
    <div class="content">
      <section class="intro">
        <p>
          Hi, I’m <a href="https://samfeldstein.xyz"
            ><strong>Sam Feldstein</strong></a
          >. I’m a bookseller at <a href="https://compositionshop.com/">
            Composition shop</a
          > in Longmont, CO. I built this app because making shelf talkers is a bit
          of a pain, especially if you’re doing it with a word processor. I wanted
          to a tool that would ensure consistent formatting, was somewhat customizable,
          and easy to use.
        </p>

        <p>
          The app is pretty simple, and offers minimal customization options. If
          you’re looking for a fully customizable template, you’re better off
          using Canva or Figma.
        </p>

        <p>
          The code is <a
            href="https://github.com/samfeldstein/shelf-talkers-vue"
            >open source</a
          >, and pull requests are welcome. You can also fork it and build your
          own version.
        </p>

        <p>
          If you have questions or feedback, you can email me at <a
            href="mailto:samfeldstein@pm.me">samfeldstein@pm.me</a
          >.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 id="basics">Basic usage</h2>
        <p>
          This app is best used on a desktop, but it should work fine on your
          smartphone.
        </p>

        <p>
          Click any field to edit. <kbd>CmdP</kbd> to print on Mac.
          <kbd>CtrlP</kbd> on Windows.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong
            >Card sizes on the webpage do not correlate to card sizes on the
            printed page.</strong
          > That's because the card sizes on the webpage morph to fit different screens.
          Make sure you preview the printed page before you print.
        </p>
        <p>
          Any changes you make are stored automatically in the browser, so you
          can pick up where you left off.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 id="print">Print</h2>
        <p>
          Printing should work fine out of the box, but if anything looks funny,
          check the following:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Make sure the page orientation is set to <b>Landscape</b></li>
          <li>Hide headers and footers</li>
          <li>Set margins to <b>Default</b></li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="font">
        <h2>Change font</h2>
        <p>Or any local font?</p>
        <p>
          The app uses <a href="https://fonts.google.com/">Google Fonts</a>, so
          if you want a custom font, you have to pick it from there. Just type
          the name of any Google font (e.g. <a
            href="https://fonts.google.com/specimen/Fira+Code">Fira Code</a
          >) into the box, and click <b>Apply</b>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 id="privacy">Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Your data is stored in your browser. Nobody can see it except you.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Questions?</h2>
        <p>
          Email me at <a href="mailto:samfeldstein@pm.me">samfeldstein@pm.me</a
          >.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>

<style lang="scss">
  main {
    max-width: 80rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 2rem 8rem;
  }

  .content {
    flex: 5;

    // Line up with nav top
    p:first-of-type {
      margin-top: 0;
    }
  }

  nav.toc {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5em;

    text-wrap: nowrap;
  }
</style>
